{
  "stem": "7556.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was still the Jewish-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] get mind to how do you say it in English-- organization that was taking care of people that really had no means of supporting themselves.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were distributing food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they-- I remember that I work in-- in-- one of the parts of the-- they call it the Jewish [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Gamina. ?] They moved some people from other towns to Cracow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were supposed to find apartments for them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so this is what we were doing also, looking, going half a day from one street to another and asking how many people in that apartment, whether we can move another couple or a few children with-- with family that was living there.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So this is what we were doing when the war started, really.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not very much, to be honest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sometimes they-- they would-- just pointed out if the Jewish woman was hiding someplace, or she might, the Polish woman, peasant, go out and scream that the Jewish girl was hiding in-- in-- in her building someplace.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were not very helpful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they-- they told the Germans that the Jews were hiding.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and the Polish police.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Polish policeman was no different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was in ghetto already, I heard the Polish woman screaming, a Jewish woman worked in here!",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She just wanted to attract attention, somebody should follow her into the building.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were some that did hide the-- the Jewish, mostly the girls, even in the building next door to the one that-- that I lived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a concierge, that woman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I knew that she was hiding Jewish young girls in her apartment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were very, very few.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
